how do you repair the hole in your heart for someone you miss dearly i'm sorry you're going through this your goal is to fill the hole in your heart but believe it or not that's not your need your need is to have other acquaintances other friends to spend time with take an interest of yours art movies skiing whatever and find a club to join being around other people that you have something in common with will be good they can't give you a quick fix to your problem but they have cares of their own listen to them also maybe you could volunteer at an organization could you pour drinks or set the table at a homeless kitchen it's hard to feel your own pain when you're helping someone else another thing i believe strongly in is the gift of laughter rent a funny movie see a funny comedian bless you and i wish you well Social rule Care Bears Mother Teresa About a Boy Shaggy dog story Past teachings of Prem Rawat Altruism Homelessness Humphrey Bogart Comedy film Poker jargon Good Morning, Vietnam Yerba mate Sauna Andrew Dice Clay Shit Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Knife I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Star Wreck: In the Pirkinning Peter Cook Jon Secada Fecal incontinence Kodocha Pitaten Whose Line Is It Anyway? Current teachings of Prem Rawat Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Theory of conduct Cigarette Smoking Man Holes (book) Leasehold estate Spidey Super Stories Public policy God Save the Queen Humour W.I.T.C.H. Jewish humour Comedy The Amber Spyglass Piccolo Junior Saga Anarchism and society Lucille Ball Scientology beliefs and practices Skat Therion (band) Alcoholics Anonymous Athrun Zala Ship naming and launching Tooth One Tree Hill (TV series) EastEnders Cliff Richard Futurama (TV series - season 2) Richard Nixon Ludwig Wittgenstein Skiing Utilitarianism Ron and Fez Babe Ruth Jackass: The Movie Rat (zodiac) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hash table Toastmasters International I Love Lucy This Is Spinal Tap Malcolm Hardee Strap-on dildo Happiness Avenue Q Kevin and Kel